s":"Full hang at bottom — dead hang to activate the lats properly"},{"name":"Bulgarian Split Squat","classification":"Unilateral","sets":3,"reps":"8-10 each side","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Single-leg position control — stay tall in the hip, resist pelvic drop. Reproduces the stance phase demands of sprinting and change of direction.","notes":"Front foot far enough forward that shin stays mostly vertical. Drive through the heel at the top."},{"name":"Dead Bug","classification":"Trunk","sets":3,"reps":"8 each side","rest":"60 sec","intent":"Brace the trunk and resist extension — build lumbar stiffness and proximal stability that anchors all force production.","notes":"Slow and controlled — lumbar stays flush with the floor on every rep."}],"notes":"3 days is best used as full body — each session covers all patterns, giving every muscle 3× per week contact at manageable volume."},{"dayNumber":2,"name":"Full Body Strength — Hinge Focus","focus":"Hinge pattern primary, vertical push/pull support, trunk integrity.","exercises":[{"name":"Leg Swing + Inchworm + Hip Circle","classification":"Prep","sets":1,"reps":"10 each / 5 reps / 10 each","rest":"none","intent":"Dynamic activation through the full kinetic chain — raise tissue temperature and prime CNS readiness for power output.","notes":"Perform continuously — this is dynamic neural activation, not static stretching."},{"name":"Broad Jump","classification":"Power","sets":3,"reps":"3-4","rest":"2-3 min","intent":"Project force horizontally — drive through the floor with triple extension. Develops the acceleration phase of sprinting.","notes":"Arm swing initiates the jump — project horizontally. Reset posture before each rep."},{"name":"Conventional Deadlift","classification":"Primary","sets":4,"reps":"6-8","rest":"2 min","intent":"Hips back, lat tension before the pull — develop posterior chain stiffness and force application from the hip that transfers directly to sprinting.","notes":"Bar stays over mid-foot, lat tension before the pull"},{"name":"Barbell Bench Press","classification":"Secondary","sets":3,"reps":"8-12","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Controlled tempo, feel the target position — each rep should improve mechanics, not just accumulate fatigue.","notes":"Slight arch, retract scapula, elbows ~45-60° from torso"},{"name":"Step-Up","classification":"Unilateral","sets":3,"reps":"8-10 each side","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Drive through the elevated leg — unilateral force application and pelvic control under single-leg load.","notes":"Control the eccentric — don't drop onto the box. Tall posture throughout."},{"name":"Pallof Press","classification":"Trunk","sets":3,"reps":"10 each side","rest":"60 sec","intent":"Stay tall and resist the rotation — anti-rotation under load directly mimics the trunk demands of contact, cutting, and force transfer.","notes":"Stand or kneel — resist the rotation without leaning or shifting hips."}],"notes":"This session shifts to posterior chain primary work — hinge strength, vertical pulling, and trunk bracing to build complete structural balance."},{"dayNumber":3,"name":"Full Body Power + Conditioning","focus":"Power output, compound integration, and conditioning to close the session.","exercises":[{"name":"Leg Swing + Inchworm + Hip Circle","classification":"Prep","sets":1,"reps":"10 each / 5 reps / 10 each","rest":"none","intent":"Dynamic activation through the full kinetic chain — raise tissue temperature and prime CNS readiness for power output.","notes":"Perform continuously — this is dynamic neural activation, not static stretching."},{"name":"Medicine Ball Slam","classification":"Power","sets":3,"reps":"4-5","rest":"2 min","intent":"Maximum velocity intent on every rep — this is a neural quality session, not a fatigue session. Reset fully between reps.","notes":"Full body extension then aggressive flexion — total effort on every rep."},{"name":"Back Squat","classification":"Primary","sets":4,"reps":"6-8","rest":"2 min","intent":"Maintain stacked posture, drive vertically through the floor — builds bilateral force production that transfers to sprint and jump mechanics.","notes":"Brace hard, maintain upright torso through the descent"},{"name":"Barbell Row","classification":"Secondary","sets":3,"reps":"8-12","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Controlled tempo, feel the target position — each rep should improve mechanics, not just accumulate fatigue.","notes":"Chest up, drive elbows back — not just pulling the bar"},{"name":"Bulgarian Split Squat","classification":"Unilateral","sets":3,"reps":"8-10 each side","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Single-leg position control — stay tall in the hip, resist pelvic drop. Reproduces the stance phase demands of sprinting and change of direction.","notes":"Front foot far enough forward that shin stays mostly vertical. Drive through the heel at the top."},{"name":"Side Plank","classification":"Trunk","sets":3,"reps":"30 sec each side","rest":"60 sec","intent":"Lateral trunk stability under a sustained load — develops the lateral chain capacity needed for single-leg stiffness and change of direction."}],"notes":"This session integrates power, strength, and conditioning — delivering a complete training stimulus and preparing the body for a recovery window before the next training block."}]}	2026-04-12 21:09:59.253137+00
