ed posture, drive vertically through the floor — builds bilateral force production that transfers to sprint and jump mechanics.","notes":"Brace hard, maintain upright torso through the descent"},{"name":"Barbell Row","classification":"Secondary","sets":3,"reps":"8-12","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Controlled tempo, feel the target position — each rep should improve mechanics, not just accumulate fatigue.","notes":"Chest up, drive elbows back — not just pulling the bar"},{"name":"Bulgarian Split Squat","classification":"Unilateral","sets":3,"reps":"8-10 each side","rest":"90 sec","intent":"Single-leg position control — stay tall in the hip, resist pelvic drop. Reproduces the stance phase demands of sprinting and change of direction.","notes":"Front foot far enough forward that shin stays mostly vertical. Drive through the heel at the top."},{"name":"Side Plank","classification":"Trunk","sets":3,"reps":"30 sec each side","rest":"60 sec","intent":"Lateral trunk stability under a sustained load — develops the lateral chain capacity needed for single-leg stiffness and change of direction."}],"notes":"This session integrates power, strength, and conditioning — delivering a complete training stimulus and preparing the body for a recovery window before the next training block."}],"_buildMeta":{"frequency":3,"goal":"hypertrophy","sport":null,"sessionDuration":null}}	2026-04-16 02:00:03.459624+00
